    <section id="tribute-info">
      <p>
        Dogecoin was created in December 2013 by software engineers Billy Markus and Jackson Palmer as a light-hearted and satirical cryptocurrency inspired by the popular "Doge" meme. What started as a joke quickly grew into a vibrant and supportive online community. Unlike many other cryptocurrencies, Dogecoin became known for its friendly spirit, community-driven fundraising efforts, and use in tipping creators online.
      </p>
      <p>
        Over time, Dogecoin gained serious traction, with high-profile endorsements and widespread internet support. In 2021, it became a cultural phenomenon thanks to viral memes, tweets, and backing from Elon Musk. Despite its humorous beginnings, Dogecoin represents the power of online communities and decentralized finance.
      </p>
    </section>

